    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-12-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-12-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="822"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d822">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.014/12–2647</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary of the Air Force</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Symington</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-12-26">December 26,
                            1947</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Reference is made to your letter
                    of 11 December 1947 (CA 893.014/11–2147)<note n="9" xml:id="d822fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning proposals made by the Chinese Government for the
                    aerial mapping of certain Chinese Provinces.</p>
                <p>Please be advised that the letter of 21 November from the Department <pb
                        facs="1013" n="1003" xml:id="pg_1003"/> of the Army had previously been
                    coordinated with and does express the views of the Department of the Air
                    Force.</p>
                <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>W. <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart Symington</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
